cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

This paper presents an extension to the BeepBeep 3 event stream engine, which is a tool for runtime verification of properties on event streams. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages), which includes topics related to programming language theory and implementation, as well as software engineering. The paper also discusses parallelization strategies, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the use of multiple threads for processing event streams could be considered a form of data parallelism, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the implementation could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which includes topics related to empirical analysis and evaluation of algorithms.
